reviewText:
Pros:

-great atmosphere reminiscent of intelligent (mostly Russian) SF (Solaris, Stalker, Aelita...);
-nice, slightly arty, mostly linear story;
-being relatively short (4-6 hrs.) it does not overstay its welcome.

Cons:

-jetpack platforming is only semi-decent due to camera issues and the inability to reverse course in mid air;
-the puzzles involving the robotic arm are very easy and repetitive;
-mineral collectibles are pointless.

Conclusion:

-For the fans of thinking person's SF more interested in the story than super tight game mechanics and flashy graphics, not averse to more artistic gaming experiences in the vein of 'Papo & Yo', Contrast' or 'Dear Esther' (but with actual gameplay and fail states) - an enjoyable ride.
